\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. C. foetida} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }807 (1753). Stems 10-50 cm, branched from the base or middle. Leaves more or less hispid; basal up to 13 × 3 cm, oblanceolate, denticulate to 2-pinnate; cauline elliptical, ovate, lanceolate or linear, runcinate to deeply pinnatifid, sessile, auriculate. Capitula 1 to many. Involucre 7-16 × 4-13 mm. Ligules yellow, reddish-purple on the outer face. Achenes fusiform, of 2 kinds: marginal stout, shortly and coarsely beaked or beakless; inner longer, slender, with a slender beak.{\i  Most of Europe except the north.} Al Au Be Bl Br Bu Co Cr Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Si Tu.
