\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. PTEROTHECA (Cass.) Babcock. Pubescent annuals with slender roots. Lower leaves petiolate. Capitula solitary or few, with few to many florets. Ligules yellow, sometimes red on outer face. Receptacle with a rigid hair subtending each floret, the pits indistinct, glabrous.
\par 

